			<div class="content" id="post-content-819953">
									

<p>Hmmm. Weird… So, you eat a couple pills, and all the zinc in your body might turn to argon? I admit I don't know much about the chemistry of human anatomy, but it sounds to me like eating these pills would simply kill someone most of the time, especially if the element selected for change happens to be carbon, or oxygen. So, I'm a bit confused by the addendum; what possible molecular swap could there be that would actually be healthy? And why would you be giving most-likely-fatal SCP-pills to 191 anyhow?</p>

