<p>I know this is an old comment, but I figured I'd answer anyway for other people that might show up here.</p>
<p>One example of a potentially beneficial swap would be for, say, lead. I can't think of a particular element to change it to that still wouldn't cause harm when suddenly interjected where other atoms or molecules used to be, but seeing as how lead is universally toxic, it seems like the safest bet for replacement.</p>

